cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with time synchronization in wireless sensor networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for time reconstruction. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents a novel algorithm for reconstructing global timestamps. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with maintaining timing accuracy in uncertain run-time conditions. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns in wireless sensor networks.
